      <p class="post-subtitle">A practical guide to choosing and conducting effective user research for digital products</p>
    </header>

    <div class="post-content">
      <div class="hero-image">
        <img src="https://picsum.photos/800/400?random=130" alt="User research methods overview" />
        <p class="image-caption">The diverse landscape of user research methodologies</p>
      </div>

      <p class="lead">User research is the foundation of great design, but choosing the right method for your specific situation can be overwhelming. This guide breaks down when, why, and how to use different research approaches effectively.</p>

      <p>The key to successful user research isn't using every method available—it's selecting the right combination of techniques that will give you actionable insights within your constraints of time, budget, and access to users.</p>

      <h2>The Research Method Spectrum</h2>

      <p>Research methods exist on multiple dimensions: qualitative vs. quantitative, behavioral vs. attitudinal, and generative vs. evaluative. Understanding these dimensions helps you choose the right approach.</p>

      <div class="method-matrix">
        <div class="matrix-header">
          <h3>Research Method Matrix</h3>
          <p>Methods plotted by approach and research phase</p>
        </div>
        <div class="matrix-grid">
          <div class="matrix-quadrant discover">
            <h4>Discover</h4>
            <div class="methods-list">
              <div class="method-item">User Interviews</div>
              <div class="method-item">Ethnographic Studies</div>
              <div class="method-item">Diary Studies</div>
              <div class="method-item">Journey Mapping</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-quadrant explore">
            <h4>Explore</h4>
            <div class="methods-list">
              <div class="method-item">Card Sorting</div>
              <div class="method-item">Tree Testing</div>
              <div class="method-item">Concept Testing</div>
              <div class="method-item">First Click Tests</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-quadrant test">
            <h4>Test</h4>
            <div class="methods-list">
              <div class="method-item">Usability Testing</div>
              <div class="method-item">A/B Testing</div>
              <div class="method-item">Prototype Testing</div>
              <div class="method-item">Accessibility Testing</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-quadrant listen">
            <h4>Listen</h4>
